      "text": "Morning (09:00:00) in the Whispering Archives\u2014you spend an productive hour among the public stacks, running your fingers along weathered spines and cross-referencing catalog entries. Most volumes are mundane: histories of forgotten kingdoms, agricultural treatises, astronomical observations from centuries past.\n\nBut tucked behind a false panel in a dusty history of the Mage Wars, you discover something intriguing: a marginal note in faded ink. \"The Seventeen Silences\u2014banned by the Conclave of 843, all copies destroyed. See restricted catalog, case 7, row 12.\"\n\nYour heart quickens. The lost codex isn't merely hidden\u2014it's been deliberately erased from history. Someone went to great lengths to bury this knowledge.\n\nAs you copy the reference into your notes, you notice Thalindor watching you more closely now. The elf's ears are twitchy, his fingers drumming against his desk. When your eyes meet, he quickly looks away.\n\nThe restricted section is now open.",
